hotkey extension to tcl/tk for x11

* build requirements

tcl/tk development library
x11 development library
c compiler
make

* build shared library

make

* usage

hotkey::register keycode modifiers script
hotkey::unregister keycode modifiers

* example code

load ./libhotkey.so
# after finish creation of the tkwindow, add hotkey alt+a
after 100 {hotkey::register 38 8 {puts hello}}

* notes

keycode and modifiers are arguments of XGrabKey(3).
you can use xev commmand to check keycode and modifiers(state).
modifiers is shift: +1, control: +4, alt: +8, mod4: +64.
